Package com.bluegosling.streams

An alternate stream implementation that includes additional operations, including simple mechanisms to define new operators.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FluentStream<T>
    A fluent stream is a Stream that provides extra operations, including extensibility in the ability to define new intermediate operators.
    StreamBridge<T,U>
    A stream bridge provides a non-trivial intermediate operation, or stage, in a stream.
    StreamNode<T,U>
    A node in a stream pipeline.
    StreamNode.Upstream<T>
    The interface used to pull data from an upstream node.
    StreamOperator<T,U>
    A stream operator provides a simple intermediate operation, or stage, in a stream.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractStreamNode<T,U>
    A useful base class for StreamNode implementations.

Package com.bluegosling.streams Description

An alternate stream implementation that includes additional operations, including simple mechanisms to define new operators.
